30/04/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis and Turkish counterpart Abdullah Gul met in Sofia on Friday (28 April), within the framework of a NATO meeting. 
Bakoyannis said that both she and Gul described their discussion, mainly on economic co-operation, as "constructive" and "very useful". 
Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan is expected to visit Thessaloniki this week for a meeting of the South East European Co-operation Process countries. 
(Kathimerini - 29/04/06; ANA - 28/04/06)
